			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>Lang-n-Prove: A DSL for Language Proofs</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MatteoCimini.html">Matteo Cimini</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567514">10.1145/3567512.3567514</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It proposes a principled way to construct and reuse proofs about language properties.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> The work introduces a meta-level DSL to express reusable proof schemas across languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The proof schemas are expressed as a DSL with an interpreter/tool support.
</li></ul></li></ul>
